## 7. Error Handling & Recovery

### 7.1 Failure Categories

| Category | Description | Retry Strategy |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| **Transient** | Temporary issues (network, rate limits) | Immediate retry with backoff |
| **Resource** | Resource exhaustion (OOM, disk full) | Escalate to manager, retry later |
| **Logic** | Code errors, invalid input | No retry, fail fast |
| **Permission** | Auth failures, missing capabilities | Escalate to permission broker |
| **Dependency** | External service failure | Circuit breaker + retry |

### 7.2 Checkpoint Recovery

Workflows can resume from checkpoints after crashes.

```typescript
interface Checkpoint {
  checkpointId: string;
  workflowId: string;
  stepId: string;           // Last completed step
  context: WorkflowContext; // Full context at checkpoint
  timestamp: string;
}

// Recovery process:
// 1. On startup, query incomplete workflows
// 2. For each, load latest checkpoint
// 3. Verify stepId still in definition
// 4. Resume from next step
```

